- How it works
A. The sender generates plain text
B. Encrypt it using a public key
C. Recipient decrypts the encrypted text using a private key
D. The recipient receives the plain text

- Online PGP tool: pgptool.org

Instructions:
A. use a FAKE name and REAL e-mail address
B. Algorithm: RSA (safer)
C. Key-size: 4096 bits

- Or: Download from: https://www.gnupg.org/

Ref:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h4hHHb6Jbb4

